ub-pr-review</command-name>\"},\"uuid\":\"58f772d7-5d14-4c26-8c36-f39dfcd49cc9\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T04:28:40.781Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"58f772d7-5d14-4c26-8c36-f39dfcd49cc9\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"19d1c506-72ed-4b7d-b66c-fb6506c3a021\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"refactoring-transcript-reads\",\"slug\":\"jolly-noodling-swing\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Base directory for this skill: /Users/alex/.claude/plugins/cache/entire-internal/entire-internal/1.0.0/skills/github-pr-review\\n\\n# GitHub PR Review\\n\\nGitHub PR interaction via `gh` CLI. For *evaluating* feedback, use `superpowers:receiving-code-review`.\\n\\n## Commands\\n\\nScript paths are relative to this skill's base directory — resolve to full paths when invoking.\\n\\n### Review threads (inline code comments)\\n\\n| Operation | Command |\\n|-----------|---------|\\n| Get PR context | `pr-info` → `{owner_repo, number, author}` |\\n| Unresolved threads | `pr-threads <owner/repo> <pr>` |\\n| Threads needing response | `pr-threads <owner/repo> <pr> <author>` |\\n| All threads (inc. resolved) | `pr-threads <owner/repo> <pr> --all` |\\n| Read a thread | `pr-thread <thread_id>` → `{path, line, diff_hunk, is_resolved, comments}` |\\n| Reply to a thread | `pr-reply <owner/repo> <pr> <reply_to_id> <body>` |\\n\\n`thread_id` and `reply_to_id` come from `pr-threads` output.\\n\\n### General PR conversation\\n\\n| Operation | Command |\\n|-----------|---------|\\n| PR conversation comments | `pr-comments <owner/repo> <pr>` → `[{id, author, body}]` |\\n\\n### PR management\\n\\n| Operation | Command |\\n|-----------|---------|\\n| Create PR | `gh pr create --title \\\"T\\\" --body \\\"B\\\" [--draft]` |\\n| Mark ready / draft | `gh pr ready [--undo] [number]` |\\n| Edit PR | `gh pr edit [number] --title \\\"T\\\" --body \\\"B\\\"` |\\n\\n## Workflow: Respond to PR Review\\n\\n1. **Get context:** `pr-info`\\n2. **Fetch threads needing response:** `pr-threads` with author filter\\n3. **For each thread:** `pr-thread` to read full conversation + diff context\\n   - Group related threads (e.g. same line from multiple comments)\\n   - Use `superpowers:receiving-code-review` for evaluation\\n   - IMPORTANT: Step through grouped feedback one by one with the user\\n   - Fix code and/or note reply\\n4. **Commit and push fixes** (need commit shas for replies)\\n5. **If rebased:** re-fetch threads — comment IDs change after force-push\\n6. **Reply to each thread:** `pr-reply` using `reply_to_id` from thread, with commit ref + description\\n7. Ask if ready to mark PR as ready for review\\n\\n## Common Mistakes\\n\\n| Mistake | Fix |\\n|---------|-----|\\n| Top-level reply | Use `pr-reply` (hits `/comments/{id}/replies`, not `/comments`) |\\n| Wrong ID for reply | Use `reply_to_id` from `pr-threads` output, not `thread_id` |\\n| Re-responding to threads | Pass author arg to `pr-threads` to filter |\\n| Forgetting to reply after fix | Always reply to confirm fix |\\n| 404 after rebase | Re-fetch threads — IDs change after force-push |\\n\\n## Setup (One-Time)\\n\\nFine-grained PAT at github.com → Settings → Developer settings → Fine-grained tokens:\\n\\n| Permission | Level |\\n|------------|-------|\\n| Pull requests | Read & Write |\\n| Contents | Read |\\n\\nPermissions are configured in the plugin's `settings.json`.\\n\"}]},\"isMeta\":true,\"uuid\":\"c655cd25-cb1c-433d-90fb-b47f9acb3f8c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T04:28:40.781Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c655cd25-cb1c-433d-90fb-b47f9acb3f8c\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"19d1c506-72ed-4b7d-b66c-fb6506c3a021\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"refactoring-transcript-reads\",\"slug\":\"jolly-noodling-swing\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01BMvMtpMdmoDMovLT2H